OL,3,CEleanor Donaldson ruled unfit to stand
OL,4,Ctrial
OL,6,FEleanor Donaldson, 60, is now set to
OL,7,Fface a trial of the facts ` a process
OL,8,Fthat tests the evidence in the case
OL,9,Fbut cannot result in her being
OL,10,Fcriminally convicted.
OL,12,FA trial of facts is a provision under
OL,13,Fthe 1986 Mental Health Order allowing
OL,14,Ffor the evidence to be put before a
OL,15,Fjury. The accused does not take part
OL,16,Fin the proceedings and can not be
OL,17,Ffound guilty. Instead, the jury is
OL,18,Fasked to determine if they committed
OL,19,Fthe offence. And although they can not
OL,20,Fbe convicted, they can be acquitted.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/5
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
